tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE volunteer_contributions (
    volunteer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    volunteer_name VARCHAR(50),
    contribution_date DATE,
    duration_hours FLOAT,
    impact_points INT
)

CREATE TABLE ImpactData (
    impact_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    volunteer_id INT,
    impact_type TEXT,
    impact_description TEXT,
    impact_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (volunteer_id) REFERENCES VolunteerContributions(volunteer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE contributions (
    contribution_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    volunteer_id INT NOT NULL,
    contribution_date DATE NOT NULL,
    hours_spent FLOAT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Contributions (
    contribution_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    volunteer_id INT NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL,
    amount DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE ImpactData (
    impact_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    contribution_id INT NOT NULL,
    metric VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    value DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    date DATE NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE Volunteer (
  volunteer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100),
  age INT,
  address VARCHAR(255),
  email VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE Contribution (
  contribution_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  volunteer_id INT,
  amount DECIMAL(10, 2),
  date DATE,
  description VARCHAR(255),
  FOREIGN KEY (volunteer_id) REFERENCES Volunteer(volunteer_id)
)

CREATE TABLE Impact (
  impact_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  contribution_id INT,
  impact_description TEXT,
  impact_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (contribution_id) REFERENCES Contribution(contribution_id)
)

CREATE TABLE Activity (
  activity_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  activity_name VARCHAR(100),
  date DATE,
  location VARCHAR(255),
  impact_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (impact_id) REFERENCES Impact(impact_id)
)

CREATE TABLE Organization (
  org_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  org_name VARCHAR(100),
  website VARCHAR(255),
  address VARCHAR(255),
  contact_name VARCHAR(100),
  contact_email VARCHAR(100)
)
